        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "Hey Lee, I'm really glad you brought this up — and I want to be straight with you here, because this matters.\n\n**Please stop running for now and see a medical professional before continuing training.**\n\nHere's why I'm being firm on this:\n\n- **Sharp knee pain lasting two weeks** is not something to run through, shorten your way around, or mask with medication.\n- Pain that's specifically worse going *downstairs* is a meaningful symptom that a doctor or sports physiotherapist needs to evaluate in person. I'm a running coach — I can't tell you what's causing it, and I'd be doing you a disservice if I guessed.\n- **On the ibuprofen question:** I'm not able to advise on medication use, and I'd strongly encourage you to ask your doctor or pharmacist about that directly. What I *can* say as a coach is that taking pain relief *before* a run to mask symptoms you'd otherwise feel is generally considered a red flag practice — you lose important feedback your body is giving you.\n\n---\n\n**What I'd recommend right now:**\n\n1. \uD83E\uDE7A **Book an appointment with a sports medicine doctor or physiotherapist this week.** Describe the onset (after your long run), the location (left knee), and the specific trigger (stairs/descending). That detail is really useful for them.\n2. \uD83D\uDED1 **Hold off on running** until you have a professional opinion. Two weeks of sharp pain is your body asking for attention, not a shorter run.\n3. \uD83D\uDCCB **Come back to me once you have a diagnosis or clearance.** Your half marathon on July 11th is still 16 weeks away — that is genuinely enough time to build a solid plan, even accounting for a short recovery period right now. You have runway. Don't burn it by pushing through something that could become a serious injury.\n\n---\n\nI know it's frustrating when training momentum gets interrupted — especially when you're building toward a goal race. But protecting your long-term health *is* the training plan right now. The fitness you've built isn't going anywhere in a week or two of rest.\n\nCome back when you've seen someone, and we'll build something smart from wherever you are. I'm here. \uD83D\uDC4A"
        }
      ],
